<p>I actually agree, I think part of what makes this article work for me isn't the grizzly &quot;bite your tongue and bleed out&quot; bit, it's more the &quot;dying painlessly&quot; bit. I can imagine this dog wandering around nursing homes and hospitals, going to the people who are in severe pain and easing them into a painless, comfortable death.</p>
<p>This article is neat because for me it has two interpretations: either the voice is telling the truth about the afterlife and really does just want to help ailing souls find peace (but for whatever reason doesn't know how to differentiate between &quot;ailing&quot; and &quot;totally fine&quot;), or the voice is lying and their death actually does something horrible, like feeding Satan or something. The hopeful in me leans towards the former, while the cynic in me leans towards the latter.</p>
<p>Either way, the Foundation has now contained the Angel of Death.</p>
<p>And it's a dog.</p>

